      "content": "You are absolutely right to be cautious, but skipping your basal insulin is a dangerous mistake that can cause severe hypoglycemia even if your sugar is currently normal. Your body still needs insulin to manage the glucose already in your bloodstream, and without food, that insulin will cause your levels to crash overnight. You should definitely check your blood sugar before bed and consider taking a small snack if it's above 70 mg/dL, rather than skipping your dose entirely.",
